title: Prep volleyball roundup: Rocori improves to 17-1
text:

Join the Conversation To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Prep volleyball roundup: Rocori improves to 17-1 TIMES STAFF REPORT 11:01 p.m. CDT October 1, 2015 Volleyball (Photo: Times graphic) 
COLD SPRING — Elenor Holthaus and Abby Templin each had 13 kills as Rocori (8-0, 17-1) defeated Sartell 3-0 in Central Lakes Conference prep volleyball action Thursday night at Rocori High School. 
Match scores were 25-10, 25-13, 25-14. 
“We served well and we passed extremely well,” Spartans coach Ted Faber said. 
Morgan Holthaus added 10 kills and 22 set assists. Abby Lieser had 11 digs and two ace serves. 
Olivia Wheeler had eight kills to lead the Sabres. Jaden Turner added six. 
WILLMAR 3, ST. CLOUD 2 
WILLMAR — Megan Taylor had 29 set assists and 16 digs, but St. Cloud Tech fell to Willmar in Central Lakes Conference play. 
Game scores were 25-22, 22-25, 25-15, 23-25, 16-14. Paige Fashant added 13 kills and Rachel Evavold had 13 digs. Kate Knowles had eight kills and three ace blocks. 
SAUK RAPIDS 3, ST. CLOUD APOLLO 0 
SAUK RAPIDS — Kyra Harvey finished with 12 kills as Sauk Rapids swept St. Cloud Apollo. 
Game scores were 25-17, 25-23, 25-10. 
Bailey Becker added eight kills, Morgan Held had 18 set assists and Kahlen Manthey finished with 24 digs for the Storm (4-4, 7-7). 
Granite Ridge 
ST. CLOUD CATHEDRAL 3, MORA 0 
MORA — Morgan Prom had 30 set assists and five ace serves for St. Cloud Cathedral in a Granite Ridge Conference win over Mora. 
Game scores were 25-18, 25-14, 25-18. 
Sam Laudenbach had eight kills and four aces and Sarah Bengtson and Katie Auger each had six kills for the Crusaders (5-1, 12-5). 
ALBANY 3, MILACA 0 
ALBANY — Erin Navratil had 12 digs, 11 kills and three blocks for Albany in a Granite Ridge Conference win over Milaca. 
Game scores were 25-10, 25-13, 25-20. 
Abby Wunderlich had 15 digs and six kills and Sidney Schiffler had 11 digs and went 17-for-17 serving for the Huskies (5-1, 13-5). 
BECKER 3, LITTLE FALLS 1 
LITTLE FALLS — Kalie Jergens had 18 kills, eight digs and three ace serves to lead Becker over Little Falls in a Granite Ridge Conference game. 
Game scores were 25-16, 22-25, 25-20, 26-24. 
Alexa Hanowski had 30 digs, Brinkley Zoller had 20 set assists and Daisy Kent had 17 set assists for the Bulldogs. 
FOLEY 3, ZIMMERMAN 0 
FOLEY — Haley Kelvington had 11 set assists, nine digs and went 12-for-13 serving to lead Foley past Zimmerman in a Granite Ridge Conference match. 
Game scores were 25-18, 25-19, 25-19. 
Morgan Long added 15 digs for the Falcons (3-4, 4-9). 
West Central 
SAUK CENTRE 3, MONTEVIDEO 0 
MONTEVIDEO –– Morgan Gamradt finished with five kills, 11 digs and three ace serves to lead Sauk Centre past Montevideo. 
Game scores were 25-13, 25-11, 25-19. 
Abby Olson had 10 kills and 10 digs for the Thunder Hawks. Taylor Borgerding added seven kills and 13 digs, Tayler Pfeffer finished with five kills, two ace blocks and three ace serves and Jill Klaphake had five kills and 24 set assists for the Mainstreeters (9-0, 15-2). 
MELROSE 3, MINNEWASKA 2 
MELROSE — Melrose edged Minnewaska in a West Central Conference match. 
Central Minnesota 
B-B-E 3, EV-W 0 
EDEN VALLEY — Tessa Halvorson had 35 set assists and seven digs for Belgrade-Brooten-Elrosa in a Central Minnesota Conference win over Eden Valley-Watkins. 
Game scores were 25-17, 25-12, 25-19. 
Ashley Trustheim had 17 kills and eight digs and Morgan Gronli added 10 digs and eight kills for B-B-E. 
MAPLE LAKE 3, PAYNESVILLE 2 
PAYNESVILLE — Maple Lake edged past Paynesville in a Central Minnesota Conference game. 
Game scores were 25-21, 25-10, 23-25, 19-25, 15-13. 
Sydney Riley had 32 set assists and 17 digs for Paynesville. 
HL-W-W 3, HOLDINGFORD 0 
HOWARD LAKE — Howard Lake-Waverly-Winsted cruised past Holdingford in a Central Minnesota Conference game. 
Game scores were 25-20, 25-12, 25-16. 
Prairie 
BROWERVILLE/EAGLE VALLEY 3, SWANVILLE 0 
SWANVILLE — Browerville/Eagle Valley rolled to a Prairie Conference victory. 
LP-GE 3, ROYALTON 2 
ROYALTON — Lanae Sieben had 11 kills and Brandi Kloss added 10 in Royalton’s loss to Long Prairie-Grey Eagle. 
Game scores were 15-25, 25-15, 25-15, 12-25, 15-8. 
Kayla Eli had 30 digs for the Royals and Bethany Siminski had 12 set assists for the Royals (2-5, 4-10-3). 
Nonconference 
PIERZ 3, CROSBY-IRONTON 0 
PIERZ –– Cassie Smieja had five kills and three ace serves to lead the Pioneers to a nonconference win.
